headline: Uber and DoorDash Are the Leaders in Ride-Hailing and Delivery. Buy the Stocks, Says Analyst.
summary: Food delivery and ride-hailing, the two pillars of the gig economy, have reached a stage of stable growth, according to Mizuho Securities.  “We believe both ride hailing and food delivery have passed the ‘land grabbing’ phase with relatively stable market shares among players,” wrote analyst Lloyd Walmsley.

headline: DoorDash Unveils DashMart Fulfillment Services: A New Model for Retail Growth
summary: SAN FRANCISCO, September 30, 2025--DoorDash (NASDAQ: DASH) today announced DashMart Fulfillment Services, a new way for retailers to strengthen the reach of their products and gain visibility with potential new customers. The model uses DoorDash’s network of DashMart locations to handle the entire process, from inventory management, picking, packing, and delivery by Dashers.

headline: Bringing Autonomy to Accuracy: DoorDash Launches SmartScale for Smarter Deliveries
summary: SAN FRANCISCO, September 30, 2025--Today, DoorDash introduced SmartScale, an innovative hardware solution designed to help restaurants improve order accuracy and deliver a more reliable guest experience. Developed by DoorDash Labs, SmartScale combines precise weighing technology with intelligent predictive modeling to help ensure every order matches its expected contents.
